Function pragma!: %Undefined% Session-local evaluator/configuration surface. Pragma keys select optional modes or limits for the active evaluation session; they do not redefine the core language/profile semantics of spaces or queries. For example, (pragma! search-table-mode variant) enables the current variant-table memoization mode for repeated search in this session, while other backends or future language surfaces may realize the same user-visible behavior differently.
Parameters:
  %Undefined% Pragma key as a Symbol
  %Undefined% Requested mode, limit, or payload for that key
Return: (type %Undefined%) Unit when the pragma is accepted, or the original pragma form when the active language/profile leaves that key uninterpreted
Function with-space-snapshot: %Undefined% CeTTa / HE-extended snapshot-binding surface. Binds a frozen copy of a space to the first parameter while evaluating the body, so reads see the snapshot while writes can still target the live space explicitly.
Parameters:
  %Undefined% Binder or pattern that receives the snapshot space
  %Undefined% Live source space to snapshot
  %Undefined% Body evaluated with the snapshot binding in scope
Return: (type %Undefined%) Results produced by evaluating the body against the snapshot-bound space
Function include: %Undefined% Loads a module into a space transactionally. The one-argument form (include spec) merges into &self. The two-argument form (include &dst spec) merges into an already-existing named space; on failure the target space is rolled back unchanged. Relative specs may resolve to .metta or .act files through the generic CeTTa loader. Raw .mm2 files stay on the explicit MORK lane for ordinary CeTTa spaces; with (pragma! mork-space-sugar allow), include on an explicit MorkSpace elaborates to the native mork:include! helper instead of lowering through generic CeTTa materialization.
Parameters:
  %Undefined% Module spec or path to include, or an explicit destination space reference followed by the module spec
Return: (type %Undefined%) Unit on success, or an Error value on failure
Function import!: (-> Atom Atom (->)) Loads a module into &self or a fresh &name. CeTTa keeps imports transactional when materializing into existing spaces; fresh compiled .act imports may stay attached as compiled PathMap spaces instead of reparsing. Raw .mm2 files are not imported through the generic CeTTa surface: import! rejects .mm2 specs, while explicit MorkSpace workflows use include with sugar enabled or the direct mork:include! helper. Loader failures can surface ModuleImportCycle, ModuleParseFailed, or a module-format-specific load error.
Parameters:
  Atom Destination space reference: &self or a fresh &name
  Atom Module spec or path to import
Return: (type (->)) Unit on success, or an Error value on failure
Function MathDomainError: (-> Number Atom ErrorType) Structured runtime error constructor for invalid real-domain math calls. The first argument is the 1-based argument index, and the second is a symbolic domain constraint tag.
Parameters:
  Number 1-based argument index that violated the domain
  Atom Symbolic domain constraint tag, such as NonNegativeReal or PositiveRealNotOne
Return: (type ErrorType) ErrorType payload describing the violated real-domain contract
[(@doc-formal (@item pragma!) (@kind function) (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Session-local evaluator/configuration surface. Pragma keys select optional modes or limits for the active evaluation session; they do not redefine the core language/profile semantics of spaces or queries. For example, (pragma! search-table-mode variant) enables the current variant-table memoization mode for repeated search in this session, while other backends or future language surfaces may realize the same user-visible behavior differently.") (@params ((@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Pragma key as a Symbol")) (@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Requested mode, limit, or payload for that key")))) (@return (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Unit when the pragma is accepted, or the original pragma form when the active language/profile leaves that key uninterpreted")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item with-space-snapshot) (@kind function) (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "CeTTa / HE-extended snapshot-binding surface. Binds a frozen copy of a space to the first parameter while evaluating the body, so reads see the snapshot while writes can still target the live space explicitly.") (@params ((@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Binder or pattern that receives the snapshot space")) (@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Live source space to snapshot")) (@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Body evaluated with the snapshot binding in scope")))) (@return (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Results produced by evaluating the body against the snapshot-bound space")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item include) (@kind function) (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Loads a module into a space transactionally. The one-argument form (include spec) merges into &self. The two-argument form (include &dst spec) merges into an already-existing named space; on failure the target space is rolled back unchanged. Relative specs may resolve to .metta or .act files through the generic CeTTa loader. Raw .mm2 files stay on the explicit MORK lane for ordinary CeTTa spaces; with (pragma! mork-space-sugar allow), include on an explicit MorkSpace elaborates to the native mork:include! helper instead of lowering through generic CeTTa materialization.") (@params ((@param (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Module spec or path to include, or an explicit destination space reference followed by the module spec")))) (@return (@type %Undefined%) (@desc "Unit on success, or an Error value on failure")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item import!) (@kind function) (@type (-> Atom Atom (->))) (@desc "Loads a module into &self or a fresh &name. CeTTa keeps imports transactional when materializing into existing spaces; fresh compiled .act imports may stay attached as compiled PathMap spaces instead of reparsing. Raw .mm2 files are not imported through the generic CeTTa surface: import! rejects .mm2 specs, while explicit MorkSpace workflows use include with sugar enabled or the direct mork:include! helper. Loader failures can surface ModuleImportCycle, ModuleParseFailed, or a module-format-specific load error.") (@params ((@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Destination space reference: &self or a fresh &name")) (@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Module spec or path to import")))) (@return (@type (->)) (@desc "Unit on success, or an Error value on failure")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item MathDomainError) (@kind function) (@type (-> Number Atom ErrorType)) (@desc "Structured runtime error constructor for invalid real-domain math calls. The first argument is the 1-based argument index, and the second is a symbolic domain constraint tag.") (@params ((@param (@type Number) (@desc "1-based argument index that violated the domain")) (@param (@type Atom) (@desc "Symbolic domain constraint tag, such as NonNegativeReal or PositiveRealNotOne")))) (@return (@type ErrorType) (@desc "ErrorType payload describing the violated real-domain contract")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item ModuleImportCycle) (@kind function) (@type (-> String ErrorType)) (@desc "Structured runtime error constructor for cyclic module imports.") (@params ((@param (@type String) (@desc "Resolved module path, shown relative to the active script or project root when possible")))) (@return (@type ErrorType) (@desc "ErrorType payload describing the detected import cycle")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item ModuleParseFailed) (@kind function) (@type (-> String ErrorType)) (@desc "Structured runtime error constructor for malformed module files that fail CeTTa's file parser checks.") (@params ((@param (@type String) (@desc "Resolved module path, shown relative to the active script or project root when possible")))) (@return (@type ErrorType) (@desc "ErrorType payload describing the module parse failure")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item sqrt-math) (@kind function) (@type (-> Number Number)) (@desc "Square root over the reals. Negative input returns (MathDomainError 1 NonNegativeReal) instead of a silent NaN.") (@params ((@param (@type Number) (@desc "Input real number")))) (@return (@type Number) (@desc "Square root as a Number when the input is within the real domain")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item log-math) (@kind function) (@type (-> Number Number Number)) (@desc "Logarithm over the reals. The base must be positive and not equal to 1, and the input must be positive; otherwise CeTTa returns a MathDomainError.") (@params ((@param (@type Number) (@desc "Logarithm base")) (@param (@type Number) (@desc "Input value")))) (@return (@type Number) (@desc "Logarithm result as a Number when both arguments are in the real domain")))]
[(@doc-formal (@item pow-math) (@kind function) (@type (-> Number Number Number)) (@desc "Exponentiation over the reals. Negative bases require integral exponents, and zero cannot be raised to a negative power; invalid combinations return MathDomainError.") (@params ((@param (@type Number) (@desc "Base")) (@param (@type Number) (@desc "Exponent")))) (@return (@type Number) (@desc "Exponentiation result as a Number when the arguments are within the real domain")))]
